Lagos, 16 January 2020, Nigeria’s premier and leading financial services provider, First Bank of Nigeria Limited, has announced that within the last year, it has supported educational institutions in the country with loans in the sum of over 10 billion naira. <img class="size-medium wp-image-32615 aligncenter" src="https://hallmarknews.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/FirstBank_Logo-1-1024x351-1-420x144.jpg" alt="" width="420" height="144" srcset="https://hallmarknews.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/FirstBank_Logo-1-1024x351-1-420x144.jpg 420w, https://hallmarknews.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/FirstBank_Logo-1-1024x351-1-150x51.jpg 150w, https://hallmarknews.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/FirstBank_Logo-1-1024x351-1-768x263.jpg 768w, https://hallmarknews.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/FirstBank_Logo-1-1024x351-1-640x219.jpg 640w, https://hallmarknews.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/FirstBank_Logo-1-1024x351-1-681x233.jpg 681w, https://hallmarknews.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/FirstBank_Logo-1-1024x351-1-1021x351.jpg 1021w, https://hallmarknews.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/FirstBank_Logo-1-1024x351-1.jpg 1024w" sizes="(max-width: 420px) 100vw, 420px" />The Bank’s support is carried out through its FirstEdu product, an educational solution created to enhance the educational facilities in schools with a view to improving the quality of education across the country. FirstEdu loan is targeted at private Nursery, Primary and Secondary schools to assist the schools in achieving their desired growth in the medium and long-term. The product provides funding to replace old furniture and equipment, pay staff salaries, purchase brand new or fairly-used buses as well as refurbish dilapidated buildings and classroom blocks. With this product, school owners/proprietors can stay ahead to make learning easy and conducive for students. The product enables the schools to access facilities with no tangible collateral, apart from domiciliation of school fees account with the Bank. <img class="size-medium wp-image-32616 alignright" src="https://hallmarknews.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/First-Bank-supports-schools-420x233.jpg" alt="" width="420" height="233" srcset="https://hallmarknews.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/First-Bank-supports-schools-420x233.jpg 420w, https://hallmarknews.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/First-Bank-supports-schools-150x83.jpg 150w, https://hallmarknews.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/First-Bank-supports-schools-768x427.jpg 768w, https://hallmarknews.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/First-Bank-supports-schools-756x420.jpg 756w, https://hallmarknews.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/First-Bank-supports-schools-640x356.jpg 640w, https://hallmarknews.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/First-Bank-supports-schools-681x378.jpg 681w, https://hallmarknews.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/First-Bank-supports-schools.jpg 900w" sizes="(max-width: 420px) 100vw, 420px" /> On the other hand, FirstEdu portal is a modular and robust web-based enterprise portal that enables Tertiary educational institutions manage academic, administrative, professional, logistics and payment challenges. The product features and benefits include; e-Learning, virtual library and facilitation of exchange programmes with foreign educational institutions; academic & student events/time-table/calendar management; school fees payment via the internet; online information and result checking; interactive community forum between students and teachers. It also affords applicants the opportunity of enrolling from the comfort of their homes or any location around the world; no licensing, installation and maintenance cost and plugs avenues for revenue leakages amongst others.  <img class="size-medium wp-image-32620 alignleft" src="https://hallmarknews.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/Chuma-Ezirim-CFA-400x300.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="300" srcset="https://hallmarknews.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/Chuma-Ezirim-CFA-400x300.jpg 400w, https://hallmarknews.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/Chuma-Ezirim-CFA-150x113.jpg 150w, https://hallmarknews.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/Chuma-Ezirim-CFA-560x420.jpg 560w, https://hallmarknews.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/Chuma-Ezirim-CFA-80x60.jpg 80w, https://hallmarknews.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/Chuma-Ezirim-CFA-100x75.jpg 100w, https://hallmarknews.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/Chuma-Ezirim-CFA-180x135.jpg 180w, https://hallmarknews.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/Chuma-Ezirim-CFA-238x178.jpg 238w, https://hallmarknews.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/Chuma-Ezirim-CFA-640x480.jpg 640w, https://hallmarknews.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/Chuma-Ezirim-CFA-681x511.jpg 681w, https://hallmarknews.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/Chuma-Ezirim-CFA.jpg 700w" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" />According to Chuma Ezirim, Group Executive, e-Business & Retail Products, First Bank of Nigeria Limited, “With FirstEdu, private schools across the various tiers of education in Nigeria; elementary, secondary and tertiary, have the right tool to boost their business to the level they desire. We are pleased to have already disbursed over N10 billion loans to schools in one year and we would continue to support growth in this key sector of our economy.”  “At FirstBank, we identify with the impact of the educational sector on the socio-economic activities of the country and importantly the lives of everyone. We remain committed to supporting schools as education is the core and root factor at enabling growth of our economy” he concluded. In need of the right educational solutions to give your school a boost, visit the FirstBank branch nearest to you or contact us on our social media channels; @firstbanknigeria on Instagram; @firstbankngr on twitter and FirstBankofNigeriaLimited on Facebook.  